        "whatBannerText": "What exactly is Web Development?",
        "whatBannerDesc": "Find out what web is and what we use it for!",
        "what": [
            {
                "id": "intro-text",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/codingImage1.png",
                "text": "Websites are an integral part of modern technology! they provide businesses with an online presence and provide as an easy place for people to find information!"
            },
            {
                "id": "code-electricity",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/codingImage2.png",
                "text": "Most people know what a website is, but a lot don't understand how they work."
            },
            {
                "id": "front-end-back-end-design",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/codingImage3.png",
                "text": "Websites are very complex, but they can broken into 3 parts. The front-end , the back-end and the design."
            },
            {
                "id": "back-end",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/codingImage4.png",
                "text": "The back end or the server side is the part of a website you don't see. The back-end communicates with the front end to send and recieve information so it can be displayed!"
            },
            {
                "id": "back-end-cont",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/codingImage5.png",
                "text": "The back end also works to keep our websites secure, by keeping our personal information safe and storing it in a secure location!"
            },
            {
                "id": "front-end",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "The front end us the part of the website you do see! The front end developer focuses on all sides of the site that the user will directly interact with."
            },
            {
                "id": "front-end-cont",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "This includes text, images, navigation, buttons, colours, animations and much more!"
            },
            {
                "id": "web-design",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "The designer is the person who figure out how a website will look. Including how things are laid out, what colours will be used and everything inbetween!"
            },
            {
                "id": "web-design-cont",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "The designer will then hand their design over to the front end developer, who will use this to build the front end functionality for the site."
            },
            {
                "id": "web-host",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Once a website is fully developed, it is then ready to be hosted on the web!"
            },
            {
                "id": "web-host-cont",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "To do this, a web server will run the sites code behind the scenes and make it so it can be accessed on the live web!"
            },
            {
                "id": "web-host-cont2",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "The site can be accessed by it's 'URL' which is its unique web address. An example is Facebook who use 'www.Facebook.com' for their URL. "
            }
        ],
        "whyBannerText": "Why do we use web development?",
        "whyBannerDesc": "Find out why we use web development",
        "why": [
            {
                "id": "explained",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "As previously mentioned, web development is made of 3 parts, which all link together to provide a website with complete functionality."
            },
            {
                "id": "explained-2",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "These parts are named the front-end, the back-end and the design."
            },
            {
                "id": "back-end-explained",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Back end development focuses on how the site works behind the scenes. The back end programmers responsibilities will likely include creating code to interact with a database, keeping the site secure and communicating with the front-end of the site."
            },
            {
                "id": "front-end-explained",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Front end development focus on building the interface for a website. The stuff that the user will see and use, like buttons, navigation and images! The front end developer will program the interface with the use of HTML/CSS/JavaScript so that a user can interact with it directly."
            },
            {
                "id": "web-design-explained",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "A web designers main role is to create a suitable web design. Their jobs may include designing the site for the users experience and usability. Designers often use software such as PhotoShop and Illustrator to create detailed designs for a developer to use."
            },
            {
                "id": "web-domain",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "Once all 3 parts are put together the website is then ready to go live! To do this, a domain name is required which can be obtained from a domain registrar. These give a website a unique online name which can be found in the form of its URL."
            },
            {
                "id": "web-hosting",
                "image": "/images/mainContentImages/robotics2.svg",
                "text": "The final step is hosting the site! Web hosts exist all around the world and use a domain to connect the site to internet so it can be accessed across the world! "
            }

        ],
